column13: Rollup is a 0-1 dummy variable for whether the IPO was a rollup
VC is a dummy with 1 for VC and 2 for a subset of VC that I call growth capital
Dual is a dummy for multiple share class IPOs
Post-issue shares is listed only for dual class IPOs, and includes all share classes (basic, not fully diluted)
Internet is a dummy with 1 if it is an internet-based  company, although in recent years I have not been updating this variable
Founding is the founding date of the company
This list of U.S. IPOs is missing IPOs with an offer price of below $5.00 before 1984
In general, missing info is denoted as -9 or . or something else that should be obvious
Please bring mistakes to my attention
Note that the post-issue number of shares for ADRs is freqently wrong, in that sometimes it is based on the number
of ordinary shares and sometimes on the basis of the ADRs without adjusting for conversion ratios
In 2021-2022 over 120 corrections to dual class, founding dates, and VC-backing have been made based on input

and Laura Field and Michelle Lowry for dual class status
